In the following, the invention will be explained in detail with reference to an embodiment illustrated in the drawing figures.


FIG. 1 is a perspective view of an interior door operating system of a motor vehicle with a Bowden cable connected to the operating handle;


FIG. 2 is a perspective view, in the direction of the arrow R of FIG. 1, of the end of the Bowden cable casing to be fastened and of the holding member on the support plate of the interior door operating system when the Bowden cable is not mounted;


FIG. 3 is a view similar to FIG. 2 but showing the inserting position of the end of the Bowden cable casing to be fastened;


FIG. 4 is a view similar to FIG. 3 but showing the fastening position of the Bowden cable casing;


FIG. 5 is a sectional view along line V--V of FIG. 4;


FIG. 6 is a top view of FIG. 4 showing the fastening position of the end piece of the Bowden cable casing; and


FIG. 7 is a perspective view of the end piece of the Bowden cable casing to be fastened together with the end piece.
